    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hey @cloakedninjas – we don't get this request often but there's a workaround to pass custom attributes to your template using the [`transformItems`](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/refinement-list/js/#widget-param-transformitems) option.\r\n\r\nHere's an example:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n    container: '#brand-list',\r\n    attribute: 'brand',\r\n    transformItems: items => items.map(item => ({\r\n      ...item,\r\n      customAttribute: 'whatever', // add your own attribute\r\n    })),\r\n    templates: {\r\n      item: ({ label, customAttribute }) => `${label} – ${customAttribute}`,\r\n    },\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nLet me know if that works for you!",
